{"questionId": "d135f4bf", "correctAnswer": "76", "section": "Math", "steps": [{"title": "Translate the graph up 4 units", "content": "Translating the graph of $y=f(x)$ up 4 units adds 4 to the output: $$g(x)=f(x)+4$$."}, {"title": "Evaluate f(0)", "content": "Substitute $x=0$ into $f(x)=(x-6)(x-2)(x+6)$:<br/>$$f(0)=(0-6)(0-2)(0+6)=(-6)(-2)(6)$$<br/>Compute step by step:<br/>$$(-6)(-2)=12$$<br/>$$12\\times6=72$$<br/>Thus $$f(0)=72$$."}, {"title": "Compute g(0) and select answer", "content": "Use the translation: $$g(0)=f(0)+4=72+4=76$$.<br/>The answer is <strong>76</strong>.", "desmosExpressions": ["f(x)=(x-6)(x-2)(x+6)"]}]}